CN Distribution Part 1 analysis

Mark R. Williamson

5 September 2024

Introduction

The purpose of this analysis is to answer a variety of research hypotheses for the First paper in CN distribution.

Research hypotheses:
1) How are copy number repeats of the rRNA operon distributed in prokaryotes?
2) What is the phylogenetic signal of CN distribution?
3) Do CN distributions different across domain (Archaea vs. Bacteria)?
4) Do CN distributions cluster by taxa (for each CN)?
5) Is CN distribution predicted by genome characteristics?

##

lm_avg_beta_sum<-Pro_CN_red %>% 
  group_by(domain, CN) %>%       
  summarise(mean=mean(range_normalized),
            sd = sd(range_normalized),
            error = qt(0.975,df=n()-1)*sd/sqrt(n()),
            ul = mean + error,
            ll = mean - error)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'domain'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
print(lm_avg_beta_sum)
